Go to http://www.enthought.com/products/edudownload.php
Enter your email address
Go to the provided link.
[http://www.enthought.com/repo/.hidden_epd_installers/]

Download the appropriate file, depending on your operating system (MacOS,
Linux, SunOS, Windows) and version.  The file versions that include "_64"
in the name are for 64-bit operating systems.  To find out whether you are
running a 32-bit or 64-bit operating system:

 * Linux: type:  uname -m
   If the result is x86_64, you are running a 64-bit operating system.
   Otherwise, you are running a 32-bit operating system.
 * MacOS:  see http://support.apple.com/kb/HT4287
 * Windows:  see http://windows.microsoft.com/en-us/windows7/find-out-32-or-64-bit

Now, perform the installation
If you are running on a 64-bit machine, replace 
each instance of epd-7.3-1-rh5-x86 by epd-7.3-1-rh5-x86_64 in the below.
 * Linux:
   mkdir -p $HOME/bin/install
   cd $HOME/bin/install
   # Download or copy the file epd-7.3-1-rh5-x86.sh to that directory.
   chmod + x epd-7.3-1-rh5-x86.sh
   ./epd-7.3-1-rh5-x86.sh
   # When you see "--more--", press space (then possibly return)
   # Accept the default location for the installation.
   # Add the following line to your ~/.bashrc file:
   #   export PATH=${HOME}/bin/install/epd-7.3-1-rh5-x86/bin:${PATH}
   # Either Log out and log back in again, or run "source ~/.bashrc"
   python --version
   # Should produce:  Python 2.7.3 -- EPD 7.3-1 (64-bit)

 * MacOS:

 * Windows:
   Download the apprpriate .msi file.
   Double-click the .msi file after it is downloaded.
